IAAJ&q=cameron+douglas+born+1978+%22michael+douglas%22&dq=cameron+douglas+born+1978+%22michael+douglas%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=PTEHVajzHsKbNteXgLgL&ved=0CEkQ6AEwCQ | page=123| title= Michael Douglas: Out of the Shadows: The Unauthorised Biography| publisher= Robson Books| year=2003| first=Andy|last= Dougan}}</ref> is an [[Americans|American]] actor.\n\n== Early life and family ==\n{{BLP unsourced section|date=August 2018}}\nDouglas <!--was born in [[Santa Barbara, California]].  He--> is the elder son of actor [[Michael Douglas]] and Diandra Morrell Douglas (n\u00e9e Luker), and grandson of actor [[Kirk Douglas]] and [[Bermuda|Bermudan]] actress [[Diana Douglas|Diana Dill]]. His parents divorced in 1995.<ref>[https://www.forbes.com/2007/04/12/most-expensive-divorces-biz-cz_lg_0412celebdivorce_slide_4.html?thisSpeed=undefined 10 Most Expensive Celebrity Divorces, ''Forbers.com'', 12 April 2007]. Forbes.com (May 22, 2002). Retrieved on May 4, 2012.</ref>\n\nThrough his father's second marriage to [[Catherine Zeta-Jones]], Douglas has two paternal half-siblings, Dylan and \nCarys.\n\n=== Family tree ===\n{{Kirk Douglas family tree}}\n\n==Career==\nHe has appeared in four films: [[Jackie Chan|Jackie Chan's]] ''[[Mr. Nice Guy (1997 film)|Mr. Nice Guy]]'' (1997), ''[[It Runs in the Family (2003 film)|It Runs in the Family]]'' (2003), ''[[National Lampoon's Adam & Eve]]'' (2005) and ''Loaded'' (2008).  In ''It Runs in the Family'' he appeared together with his father, Michael Douglas, grandfather, Kirk Douglas, and grandmother, Diana Dill.\n\n==Legal troubles==\n===Drug dealing and conviction===\nDouglas has been arrested for drug offenses at least three times. In 1999, he was found with [[cocaine]] in [[Manhattan]] and was arrested and charged with a misdemeanor possession of a controlled substance.<ref>{{cite news|first=Bill|last=Hoffman|title=Michael Douglas' Son in Coke Arrest|work=New York Post|date=1999-10-28}}</ref> The charge was dropped after he pleaded guilty to the lesser charge of disorderly conduct. In 2007, he was charged with felony possession of a controlled substance after police officers found a syringe with liquid cocaine in a car he was in. On July 28, 2009, Douglas was arrested by the Drug Enforcement Administration for possession of {{convert|0.5|lbs|kg|abbr=on}} of [[methamphetamine]]. Due to the large amount of the drug seized, Douglas was charged with intent to distribute.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nypost.com/seven/08032009/entertainment/michael_douglas_son_arrested_for_meth_182809.htm |first=Tom |last=Liddy |title=Michael Douglas' Son Arrested for Meth |work=New York Post |date=2009-08-03}}</ref> The charge carries a minimum prison sentence of 10 years and a maximum of life.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/8191279.stm |title=Douglas son to face drugs trial |publisher=BBC News |date=2009-08-08 |accessdate=2009-08-08}}</ref>\n\nOn January 27, 2010, Douglas pleaded guilty to conspiracy to distribute drugs and [[heroin]] possession after his girlfriend had smuggled heroin hidden inside an electric toothbrush and passed it on to him while he was under house arrest.<ref>{{cite news | last =Tom | first = Hays | url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2010/01/27/michael-douglas-son-camer_0_n_438940.html |title=Michael Douglas' son pleads guilty to drug trafficking |agency=[[Associated Press]] |work=[[The Huffington Post]] |date=January 27, 2010 |accessdate=2013-06-02}}</ref> On April 20, 2010, Douglas was sentenced to five years in prison for possessing heroin and dealing large amounts of methamphetamine and cocaine out of a New York hotel room.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.blogs.cnn.com/2010/04/20/michael-douglas-son-cameron-gets-five-years-in-prison/?hpt=T2 |title=Michael Douglas' son Cameron sentenced to five years |publisher=News.blogs.cnn.com |date= April 20, 2010|accessdate=2013-06-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://ca.news.yahoo.com/s/reuters/100420/entertainment/centertainment_us_douglas_cameron|title=Michael Douglas's son sentenced to 5 years|date=April 20, 2013|agency=[[Reuters]] |publisher=[[Yahoo! News]] |archive-date=April 25, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100425013424/http://ca.news.yahoo.com/s/reuters/100420/entertainment/centertainment_us_douglas_cameron}}</ref> Michael Douglas publicly assumed blame for \"being a bad father\" but said that without prison intervention, Cameron \"was going to be dead or somebody was gonna kill him. I think he has a chance to start a new life, and he knows that.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalledger.com/ledgerpop/article_272631605.shtml|title=Michael Douglas and Blame Game for Son Cameron's Jail Sentence|work=National Ledger|date=May 4, 2010|accessdate=May 5, 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2011, Douglas pleaded guilty to possessing drugs in prison.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://edition.cnn.com/2011/10/21/showbiz/celebrity-news-gossip/cameron-douglas-pleads-guilty-ppl/index.html|work=CNN|title=Cameron Douglas pleads guilty to possessing drugs in prison|date=October 21, 2011}}</ref> On December 21, 2011, he was sentenced to an additional 4{{fract|1|2}} years in prison for this charge.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://nypost.com/2011/12/21/douglas-sentenced-to-another-4-12-years-for-drug-possession|title=Douglas sentenced to another 4 1/2 years for drug possession|first=Bruce|last=Golding|work=[[New York Post]]|date=December 21, 2011|accessdate=September 23, 2013}}</ref> On April 15, 2013, this extended prison sentence was affirmed by the Second U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-504083_162-57579795-504083/cameron-douglas-son-of-actor-michael-douglas-loses-appeal-to-reduce-prison-sentence-report-says/ | title=Cameron Douglas, son of actor Michael Douglas, loses appeal to reduce prison sentence, report says|work=CBS News}}</ref> In December 2012, his leg was broken by another inmate.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-504083_162-57559848-504083/michael-douglas-son-cameron-badly-injured-in-prison-report-say|title=Michael Douglas' son Cameron badly injured in prison, report say|publisher=CBS News|accessdate=2013-06-02}}</ref> In January 2013, Douglas was again found to have drugs in his system while in prison in [[Loretto, Pennsylvania]]. He failed a urinalysis and was sent to segregated housing.<ref>{{cite news|title=Michael Douglas' son Cameron busted again|url=https://nypost.com/2013/01/20/michael-douglas-son-cameron-busted-again/|work=[[New York Post]]|accessdate=January 20, 2013|first=Brad|last=Hamilton|archivedate=April 3, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403113349/http://nypost.com/2013/01/20/michael-douglas-son-cameron-busted-again|url-status=live}}</ref> In April 2013, Douglas lost an appeal to have his sentence reduced.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/408177/michael-douglas-son-cameron-douglas-loses-appeal-to-lighten-prison-sentence|title=Michael Douglas' Son, Cameron Douglas, Loses Appeal to Lighten Prison Sentence|first=Natalie|last=Finn|publisher=[[E! News]]|date=April 15, 2013|accessdate=June 2, 2013| archivedate=May 21, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140521082256/http://www.eonline.com/news/408177/michael-douglas-son-cameron-douglas-loses-appeal-to-lighten-prison-sentence| url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Release from prison===\nOn August 1, 2016, Douglas was released early from prison and transferred to a [[halfway house]] in [[New York City]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.yahoo.com/celebrity/michael-douglas-son-cameron-released-142645949.html|title=Michael Douglas' Son Cameron Released From Jail After Nearly Seven Years|publisher=US WEEKLY|date= August 1, 2016|accessdate= April 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://pagesix.com/2016/08/01/jail-did-wonders-for-michael-douglas-sons-buff-body|title=Jail did wonders for Michael Douglas' son's buff body|first1=Leonica|last1=Valentine|first2=Bruce|last2=Golding|date=August 1, 2016|work=pagesix.com|accessdate=February 28, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/people/2016/08/01/michael-douglas-son-cameron-douglas-released-from-prison/87929338|title=Reports: Michael Douglas' son Cameron released from prison|work=usatoday.com|accessdate=February 28, 2017}}</ref> after seven years behind bars,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/michael-douglas-son-cameron-released-8543156|title=Michael Douglas' son Cameron released from prison after seven years behind bars|first=Claire|last=Rutter|date=August 2, 2016|work=mirror.co.uk|accessdate=February 28, 2017}}</ref> with two of the seven years in segregated housing.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/gossip/la-et-mg-michael-douglas-cameron-douglas-released-prison-20160801-snap-story.html|title=Cameron Douglas, Michael Douglas' son, released from prison after nearly seven years|first=Christie|last=D'Zurilla|work=latimes.com|accessdate=February 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHis book, ''Long Way Home''<!--NOTE: the WP article [[A Long Way Home (book)]] is about a DIFFERENT book--> is about his experiences after being convicted on drug charges.<ref>{{cite book|last=Douglas|first=Cameron|title=Long Way Home|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jUmHDwAAQBAJ|year=2019|publisher=Knopf Doubleday Publishing Group|isbn=978-0-525-52084-9}}</ref>\nHe has set up an account on [[Instagram]], where his first post was an image of the phrase \"Be the energy you want to attract.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/gossip/la-et-mg-cameron-douglas-tattoos-20160804-snap-htmlstory.html|title=Fresh from prison, Cameron Douglas is now a ripped and tatted version of Kirk Douglas|first=Christie|last=D'Zurilla|publisher=|accessdate=28 February 2017|via=LA Times}}</ref>\n\nOn December 18, 2017, Douglas welcomed his first child, a daughter named Lua Izzy Douglas, with his girlfriend, [[Brazilians|Brazilian]] actress and yoga instructor Viviane Thibes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/parents/cameron-douglas-viviane-thibes-welcome-daughter/amp/|title=Cameron Douglas Welcomes Daughter Lua Izzy|first=Dave|last=Quinn|date=December 21, 2017|work=People|accessdate=October 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 1997\n| ''[[Mr. Nice Guy (1997 film)|Mr. Nice Guy]]''\n| Giancarlo's Man\n| Film Debut<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/movies/mr-nice-guy/cast/132984/|title=Mr. Nice Guy|work=tvguide.com|accessdate=28 February 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[It Runs in the Family (2003 film)|It Runs in the Family]]''\n| Asher Gromberg\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/it-runs-in-the-family-2003|title=It Runs in the Family|author=Roger Ebert|date=25 April 2003|work=rogerebert.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[National Lampoon's Adam & Eve]]''\n| Adam\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Loaded (2008 film)|Loaded]]''\n| Rick\n| \n|-\n|2020\n|''The Runner''\n|Detective Wall\n|''Filming''\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|234979}}\n* {{cite news|url=https://nypost.com/2016/08/07/how-cameron-douglas-went-from-hollywood-royalty-to-living-in-a-halfway-house/|title=How Cameron Douglas went from Hollywood royalty to living in a halfway house|first=Dana|last=Schuster|date=August 7, 2016|newspaper=The New York Post}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Douglas, Cameron}}\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American drug traffickers]]\n[[Category:Schuyler family]]\n[[Category:American prisoners and detainees]]\n[[Category:Douglas family]]\n[[Category:American people of Belarusian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Belgian descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Bermudian descent]]\n[[Category:Male actors f